arch dwarf_wiz
name Baalgar,dwarven mage
msg
@match hi|hello
Greetings,estimed stranger. What
brings you to my table?
@match information|info
Ah,you desire information... but on
what?
@match necromancer
Ah,the necromancer. His undead have
been a plague to our land. I suppose
you know of his foul pet,the Dark
Behemoth?
@match Dark Behemoth
Ah,yes. That foul beast was a gift
from the Devourers themselves. I do
not see how it can be deafeated. One
cannot even touch the thing without
the chance of his very soul being
sucked out of him. But of course,you
will not be foolish to attempt to kill
the thing,now will you?
@match yes
I can only hope your soul is prepared
against such great darkness. I would
try to convince you against such a
foolish attempt,but i can see you are
obstinate. May God protect you.
@match the Balrog|Balrog
Aye,the Great Balrog. I have heard
tales about him,and how he was sealed
in a great tomb under the earth. But
foolish dwarves and gnomes,desiring
more wealth and power,have delved into
the depths of the earth,even unto his
tomb. In the fabled mines of
Morgria,the dwarves have touched upon
the forbidden catacombs unto his tomb.
Though,the Balrog is still in his
chains. The great seal,blocking his
power,has been broken. With his great
power,he has taken the sanity of many
dwarven miners. The goblins who have
dwelled secretly in those ancient
caves have been drawn to him,even now
they seek to find the inner tomb and
free him. I pray a hero will come and
save our land from him.
endmsg
